(# ABC Verilog-to-AIG Step-by-Step Guide) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This guide shows how to convert a Verilog module into an AIG file with ABC on this machine.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Test workspace:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- `D:\\abc-master\\_FullAdderTest`) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Files used in the test:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- `full_adder_1bit.v`) Tj
T* (- `full_adder_1bit.aig`) Tj
T* (- `abc_full_adder_transcript.txt`) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Important note about Verilog support:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (ABC does not accept full modern Verilog syntax. Its `read_verilog` command supports an older) Tj
T* (IWLS subset.) Tj
T* (For that reason, the module header should use a plain port list and the `input`/`output`) Tj
T* (declarations should appear inside the module body.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Example of ABC-friendly Verilog:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (module full_adder_1bit \(a, b, cin, sum, cout\);) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (input a;) Tj
T* (input b;) Tj
T* (input cin;) Tj
T* (output sum;) Tj
T* (output cout;) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (assign sum = a ^ b ^ cin;) Tj
T* (assign cout = \(a & b\) | \(a & cin\) | \(b & cin\);) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (endmodule) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (## Commands used) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (From `D:\\abc-master`, run:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (.\\_TEST\\abc.exe -c "read_verilog _FullAdderTest\\full_adder_1bit.v; print_stats; strash;) Tj
T* (print_stats; write_aiger _FullAdderTest\\full_adder_1bit.aig") Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (What each command does:) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
