() Tj
T* (1. `read_verilog _FullAdderTest\\full_adder_1bit.v`) Tj
T* (   Reads the Verilog file into ABC.) Tj
T* (2. `print_stats`) Tj
T* (   Shows the network statistics after import.) Tj
T* (3. `strash`) Tj
T* (   Converts the logic network into AIG form.) Tj
T* (4. `print_stats`) Tj
T* (   Shows the AIG statistics after conversion.) Tj
T* (5. `write_aiger _FullAdderTest\\full_adder_1bit.aig`) Tj
T* (   Writes the final AIGER file.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (## How to verify the generated AIG) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Run:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (.\\_TEST\\abc.exe -c "read _FullAdderTest\\full_adder_1bit.aig; print_stats") Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If ABC reads the `.aig` file successfully and prints stats, the export worked.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (## Expected result from this tested example) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The tested full adder produced an AIG file with:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- 3 inputs) Tj
T* (- 2 outputs) Tj
T* (- 11 AND nodes) Tj
T* (- logic depth 4) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (## Common pitfall) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If you use ANSI-style Verilog such as:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (module full_adder_1bit \() Tj
T* (    input wire a,) Tj
T* (    ...) Tj
T* (\);) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (ABC may fail with an error similar to:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (`Expected closing parenthesis after "module".`) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If that happens, rewrite the module using the older port-list style shown above.) Tj
ET
endstream
